Iraqi Army Says It Detained Local Al-Qaeda Military Leader

-- B y   C a r o l i n e   A l e x a n d e r
-- 
2011-05-18T15:57:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/iraqi-army-says-it-detained-local-al-qaeda-military-leader.html
Iraq’s army arrested the military
leader of the local al-Qaeda organization in a raid near a
northern city, state-sponsored Iraqiyah television reported.  The terrorist leader, known as “Abu Radhwan,” was
detained along with associates west of Samarra, about 70 miles
(113 kilometers) north of the capital  Baghdad , according to the
report, which cited Samarra Operations Command. Further details
weren’t provided and a spokesman for the Iraqi Defense Ministry
wasn’t immediately available for comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Caroline Alexander in  London  at 
 calexander1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 